# // Steps to create and run the app

1. Create and open the root folder --> PS C:\Users\hp\Desktop\MERN Auth>
2. Create react app using --> PS C:\Users\hp\Desktop\MERN Auth> npx create-vite@latest client
   - Select a framework: react
   - Select a variant: JavaScript
   - Install with npm and start now? Yes

   Now you can run the app by using this command --> npm run dev

3. Remove uneccessary files like asset defaut images, App.css and the default file of App.jsx
   and change with the rfc (react functional component)

4. Install taiwind css and configure it by the follow the rules of tailwind css.
   PS C:\Users\hp\Desktop\MERN Auth\client> npm install tailwindcss @tailwindcss/vite

   ## Configure the Vite plugin

   import { defineConfig } from 'vite'
   import tailwindcss from '@tailwindcss/vite'
   export default defineConfig({
   plugins: [
   tailwindcss(),
   ],
   })

   Import Tailwind CSS in to index.css ---> @import "tailwindcss";

5. Move the .gitignore file from client to root folder and adjust with the following updated
   good gitignore file.

   # Logs

   logs
   _.log
   npm-debug.log_
   yarn-debug.log*
   yarn-error.log*
   pnpm-debug.log*
   lerna-debug.log*

   # Environment variables (VERY IMPORTANT)

   .env
   .env.\*

   # Dependencies

   node_modules/

   # Build outputs

   client/dist
   client/build
   server/dist
   dist-ssr

   # Local files

   \*.local

   # Optional backend folders

   uploads/
   tmp/

   # Editor directories and files

   .vscode/_
   !.vscode/extensions.json
   .idea
   .DS_Store
   _.suo
   _.ntvs_
   _.njsproj
   _.sln
   \*.sw?

6. Create Server folder for backend
7. Initialize git in the root folder by the using the following code

   git init
   git add README.md
   git commit -m "first commit"
   git branch -M main
   git remote add origin https://github.com/kalkidan-elel/Mern-Auth-Updated.git
   git push -u origin main
